history.content: When I took CS 188 last semester it didn't expand. Hopefully someone can speak on their phase 2 experience, but many of my friends who had much later appointments for phase 1 ended up dropping thinking they wouldn't get in. Before Fall 2019, CS 188 wasn't webcast so they had to keep enrollment capped at wheeler hall capacity. With possible remote instruction things could change

Does CS188 generally expand? I am currently undeclared (plan to take my last of the three classes needed for declaration in the summer and then declare at the end of the summer). I am thinking of taking 188 this Fall and will be adding the class in Phase 2. I will not get enrolment priority for the Fall, since I will be declaring at the end of the summer. Do I still stand a chance of getting the class?
